# ChangeLog

All notable changes to this project are documented in this file.

## Unreleased

Date: 2026-06-02

### Changed

- Reworked the landing page content around the Free Software Free Society message and removed the old stats, live preview, focus areas, CTA buttons, and email list sections.
- Updated project branding from "QB Networks Web Development Team" to "QB Networks" across the site and documentation.
- Switched the visible site branding and favicon to img/qbnetworks400x400.svg and removed the old colored background from the SVG artwork.
- Added ethics.html and coc.html as first-class themed pages sharing the same design system as the home page.
- Unified the main navigation across pages with Home, Ethics, and Code of Conduct links.
- Added LibreJS-friendly footer text on all public pages with direct JavaScript source, website source code, AGPLv3-or-later license, and copyright links.
- Simplified front-end behavior in script.js to keep only shared header, menu, and reveal logic after removing stats and form handling.
- Updated English and Turkish README files to reflect the current site structure, branding, and licensing details.

### Changed (2026-06-03)

- Reworked the header layout on all public pages to a centered, stacked structure: brand (logo + QB Networks) at the top and navigation links centered directly underneath.
- Removed the temporary logo-only and extra centered-logo block variants after iterative UI adjustments, keeping a consistent brand block in the header.
- Standardized brand behavior so the top QB Networks brand link on the home page now points to index.html instead of index.html#top.
- Center-aligned the home hero content so the "Free Software Free Society" heading and its supporting paragraph are visually centered.
- Reduced the hero title size for better balance with the centered layout.
- Switched site typography to a monospace stack across pages.
- Added a shared bottom "Source Code" + "Additional Links" section to index.html and coc.html to match ethics.html.
- Removed duplicate Source Code card content from coc.html so all pages use the same bottom links pattern.

